image.altText: A GWS AFL player hugs a teammate as he celebrates his own goal in a final.

props.synopsis: The Giants have stormed back into the preliminary final, kicking four straight goals to lead Collingwood at the main break. Follow live.

title.children: Greene drives Giants into the lead as Pies under pressure in prelim final

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Giants have thrown their punch, and the Pies have been rocked. That second quarter belonged to GWS, and as soon as the really frenetic heat came off the game they suddenly looked the team most prepared to play winning football. Contested ball dominance, rock-solid structure behind the ball, incredible class by hand and foot. It's everything the Giants want to see in a game, and it has flipped this contest on its head. The Pies went goalless in that second quarter, but they'll look at some bad misses as proof they are still right in it. And of course they are, it's only a 10-point game at half-time. But we've seen this before from the Giants. And they don't tend to take a backward step from here. Collingwood needs a special second half.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HT: The Giants erupt and lead by 10 points

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Jarome Luai moved to the left side, found Stephen Crichton, who held off Jahrome Hughes and flicked a delightful pass wide out to Turuva, who then passed inside to Dylan Edwards and there is no stopping the Panthers now! Cleary adds two more to make it 30-4. Game well and truly over.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 55' Dylan Edwards seals it!

children.content: (Getty Images)
Jarome Luai

moved to the left side, found Stephen Crichton, who held off Jahrome Hughes and flicked a delightful pass wide out to Turuva, who then passed inside to Dylan Edwards and there is no stopping the Panthers now!
Cleary adds two more to make it 30-4.
Game well and truly over.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Superb from Liam Martin! Jarome Luai went one way, realised the route was shut so turned around, skipped away from a couple of tackles and passed the ball to the right side where Martin picked up the ball and burst through the line after a strong fend on Cameron Munster. Nathan Cleary was on his inside and finished easily, to finish the Storm with 26 minutes remaining. He adds the extras too, the lead is 24-4.
